                        HourlyPrecipitationRepository precipitationRepository,

                        DocumentRequestService drs,
                        java.util.logging.Logger logger,
                        java.text.SimpleDateFormat simpleDateFormat)
        Creates an instance of HarvesterService.
        Parameters:
        locationRepository - The repository that stores the locations that data will be harvested for.
        precipitationRepository - The repository where precipitation data is stored.
        weatherRepository - The repository where non-precipitation weather data is stored.
        drs - The service that is used to obtain XML documents from the API.
        logger - Logs warning messages.
        simpleDateFormat - Used to parse date data using a given time zone.

    • Method Detail

      • harvestData

        public void harvestData​(java.util.Calendar calendar)
                 throws java.lang.InterruptedException
        Requests and data stores from a HARMONIE-AROME API for locations in the database.
        Parameters:
        calendar - Used to determine the time at which to store data.
        Throws:
        java.lang.InterruptedException - The service will sleep for a second if it is having problem obtaining data from the API. The exception will be thrown if the service is interrupted during this time.

      • processLocation

        public boolean processLocation​(LocationDetails location,
                               java.util.Calendar calendar)
        Requests and stores data from a HARMONIE-AROME API for a given location.
        Parameters:
        location - The location to obtain data for.
        calendar - Used to determine the times to store data for.
        Returns:
        True if the data was received and stored, false otherwise.
